## **📜 Overview**

The **Copilot News Scraper** is an **automated web-scraping system** designed to collect, filter, and organize news articles from **Black-owned media, AI fairness research, and global tech ethics sources**. This tool is built for **Obsidian integration**, ensuring **real-time, structured knowledge acquisition** with minimal manual intervention.

Designed to support **Africana Studies, AI bias mitigation, and cybersecurity research**, this scraper prioritizes **reliable, fact-checked journalism** while eliminating algorithmic noise.

---

## **🛠 Key Features**

✔ **🔗 Clickable "Go!" Links** → Instead of long URLs, CSV files now have **"Go!"** as a clickable hyperlink to the article.  
✔ **📅 Date Filtering** → Ensures only **news from the past 3 days** is collected.  
✔ **🔠 Title Optimization** → **Trims article titles to 90 characters** for clarity and structure.  
✔ **🌐 Dynamic Website Handling** → Uses **Selenium for JavaScript-heavy sites** & **BeautifulSoup for static pages**.  
✔ **📡 Bias-Aware Curation** → Scrapes from sources focusing on **Black media, AI fairness, and cybersecurity**.  
✔ **🔧 UTF-8 Encoding Fixes** → Prevents garbled characters in article titles and descriptions.

